    <string name="SectionOneTheoryDef_3">• Power with Natural Exponent: aⁿ means multiplying a by itself n times; a¹ = a. a is the base, n is the exponent.\n
• Common names: a² (square), a³ (cube).\n
• Root (Evolution): the inverse of powers. The nth root ⁿ√a gives a number whose nth power equals a. √a is the square root, ³√a the cube root.</string>
    <string name="SectionOneTheoryDefQuestion_3">What is 2⁵?</string>
    <string name="SectionOneTheoryDefAnswerOne_3">16</string>
    <string name="SectionOneTheoryDefAnswerTwo_3">32</string>
    <string name="SectionOneTheoryDefAnswerThree_3">64</string>
    <string name="SectionOneTheoryDefCorrectAnswer_3">32</string>


    <string name="SectionOneTheoryProperties_3">• Even powers of negatives are positive; odd powers stay negative.\n
• 0ⁿ = 0, 1ⁿ = 1.\n
• Some roots (like √2) are not rational.\n
• Approximate roots satisfy bⁿ &lt; a &lt; (b + α)ⁿ.</string>
