    <string name="SectionFourTheoryDef_3">• Power Rules:\n
1. aᵐ·aⁿ = aᵐ⁺ⁿ\n
2. aᵐ / aⁿ = aᵐ⁻ⁿ\n
3. (aᵐ)ⁿ = aᵐⁿ\n
4. (ab)ⁿ = aⁿbⁿ, (a/b)ⁿ = aⁿ/bⁿ\n
5. (-a)ⁿ = aⁿ if n even, -aⁿ if odd.</string>
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryDefQuestion_3">What is 3² · 3³?</string>
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryDefAnswerOne_3">3⁵</string>
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryDefAnswerTwo_3">3⁶</string>
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryDefAnswerThree_3">9⁵</string>
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryDefCorrectAnswer_3">3⁵</string>

    <string name="SectionFourTheoryProperties_3">Additional Power Properties:\n
• aᵐ⁺ⁿ = aᵐ · aⁿ (adding exponents corresponds to multiplying powers).\n
• (aᵐ)ⁿ = aᵐⁿ (a power of a power multiplies exponents).\n
• For a ≠ 0: aᵐ / aⁿ = aᵐ⁻ⁿ; in particular a⁰ = 1.\n
• Powers of products and quotients distribute over each factor.\n
• These rules hold for all integer exponents when the base is nonzero.</string>
